name: South Hall
directions: On the floor above the library and student services. When you come up the elevators, hang a left down the hall. Next make a right (this is your only option to continue down the hall), then a left at the next intersection (your options would be left or right. Right is a dead end with more classrooms.). Around your corner to the right are traditionally gendered bathrooms that have been turned into neutral restrooms with signs and locks on the doors.
comment: These are traditionally gendered bathrooms that have been adapted to neutral restrooms to meet legal requirements. The first door on your right has two stalls, a urinal, and two sinks. The door straight ahead has I think six stalls and sinks. Beware of those who still use these restrooms as gendered and do not lock the door behind them. Both are wheelchair accessible.
